<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4244] Make bin/hbase help more useful</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4244</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Talking with Doug Meil yesterday, I found out he didn&apos;t know we had an HLog or HFile analyzer.  We should add these quick links to the bin/hbase help prompt.  Additionally, we should reword the help so it&apos;s very clear what tools DBAs have at their disposal vs package/process management.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12519866">HBASE-4244</key>
            <summary>Make bin/hbase help more useful</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/improvement.png">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/minor.png">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="5" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png" description="A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.">Resolved</status>
